JOHANNESBURG - The Ennerdale father who fatally shot his son outside school this week has been released on a warning. The magistrate on a Lenasia court said the shooting is a tragedy that will haunt the accused, Sibusiso Emmanuel Tshabalala, and the rest of the family. Tshabalala is not required to post bail. He shot his 16-year-old son, Luyanda, outside the Fred Norman Secondary school on Tuesday, allegedly mistaking him for a hijacker. READ: ConCourt leaves gun laws unchanged The case will resume on 24 July. eNCA